# {{$.TerraformName}}_iam_member (list)

Lists IAM **member bindings** for a Google Cloud {{ $.Name}} for use with 
[`terraform query`](https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/cli/commands/query) and **`.tfquery.hcl`** files.

Results correspond to existing
[`{{ $.TerraformName}}_iam_member`](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/google/latest/docs/resources/{{$.TerraformName}}_iam)
managed resources.

For how list resources work in this provider, file layout, Terraform version requirements, and 
shared `list` block arguments, refer to the guide 
[Use list resources with terraform query (Google Cloud provider)](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/google/latest/docs/guides/using_list_resources_with_terraform_query).

## Example

```hcl
list "{{$.TerraformName}}_iam_member" "all" {
  provider = {{ if eq $.MinVersion "beta" }}google-beta{{ else }}google{{ end }}

  config {
    {{ underscore $.IamPolicy.ParentResourceAttribute }} = "my-{{ underscore $.IamPolicy.ParentResourceAttribute }}"
  }
}
```

Run `terraform query` from the directory that contains the `.tfquery.hcl` file.

## Configuration (`config` block)

* {{ underscore $.IamPolicy.ParentResourceAttribute }} - The parent {{ $.Name }} identifier used to scope IAM member bindings.
* role - Optional IAM role filter
* member - Optional IAM member filter


## Results

By default each result includes **resource identity** for [`{{$.TerraformName}}_iam_member`](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/google/latest/docs/resources/{{$.TerraformName}}_iam) (see [Resource identity](https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/language/resources/identities)).

With `include_resource = true` on the `list` block, results also include the full resource-style attributes documented for the managed [`{{$.TerraformName}}_iam_member` resource](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/google/latest/docs/resources/{{$.TerraformName}}_iam#attributes-reference).